02/06/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The two largest ruling coalition parties agreed Tuesday (1 June) on a draft constitution for Serbia, according to Deputy Prime Minister Miroljub Labus. The Democratic Party of Serbia, headed by Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica, and Labus's G17 Plus will arrange discussions with other parties in the coalition before submitting the draft to parliament. Labus said that the government is doing all it can to adopt the new constitution, but added that the Serbian Radical Party is blocking work at the committee level. (B92, Tanjug - 01/06/04)
